trashday.model

Class Calendar

  • java.lang.Object
    • trashday.model.Calendar

  • public class Calendar
extends Object
    Data structure for a regular pickup schedule. Use an iCalendar-based calendar representation to allow for future integration options and recurring event handling.

    NOTE: The calendar and its events do NOT keep associated time zone information. This keeps time zone management outside of the Calendar storage model.

    Author:
    J. Todd Baldwin
    See Also:
    iCal4j, iCal4j Javadocs, Jackson Module: Model Versioning, RFC 5545: Internet Calendaring and Scheduling Core Object Specification (iCalendar)

      • has

        public Boolean has(CalendarEvent newEvent)
        Test if this event already exists in the calendar. Checks to find any event that has same summary (pickup name) and matching RRULE.

        A generalized algorithm would be better. Since there is already an ical4j open issue, I'm just doing something sufficient for events created within this one application. If/when the application starts integrating with external iCalendars, this needs to be upgraded to handle generalized cases.

        Assertions for all existing calendar entries: Events are always active. No RRULE COUNTs or DTENDs. Assertions for all newEvents: Events are always active. No RRULE COUNTs or DTENDs. One and only one RRULE per event One and only one entry in BYDAY or BYMONTHDAY in the RRULE RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=TU RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;INTERVAL=1;BYDAY=TU RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;INTERVAL=2;BYDAY=TU RRULE:FREQ=MONTHLY;BYMONTHDAY=1 RRULE:FREQ=MONTHLY;BYMONTHDAY=-3 RRULE:FREQ=MONTHLY;BYDAY=1FR

        Parameters:
        newEvent - CalendarEvent the we are checking may already have a "duplicate" in the calendar.
        Returns:
        true if this newEvent already exists in the calendar.
        See Also:
        Can ical4j identify exceptions to recurring calendar events?

      • pickupAddBiWeekly

        public Boolean pickupAddBiWeekly(LocalDateTime ldtEvent,
                                 String pickupName,
                                 boolean nextWeek,
                                 DayOfWeek dow,
                                 LocalTime tod)
        Add a pickup time that repeats every other week.
        Parameters:
        pickupName - of this pickup
        ldtEvent - LocalDateTime of this event start
        nextWeek - false to start this pickup on this coming dow. true to start this pickup on thefollowing day this dow occurs. For example, if today is Monday and dow=Friday, a false next week means this coming Friday and a true means the Friday after this coming Friday.
        dow - DayOfWeek when this pickup time recurs.
        tod - LocalTime time-of-day when this pickup time recurs
        Returns:
        true if added successfully, false if a duplicate of this event already exists in the calendar.

      • pickupAddDayOfMonth

        public Boolean pickupAddDayOfMonth(LocalDateTime ldtRequest,
                                   String pickupName,
                                   Integer dom,
                                   LocalTime tod)
        Add a pickup time that repeats on a given day of month.
        Parameters:
        pickupName - of this pickup
        ldtRequest - LocalDateTime the starting date of this pickup. The actual calendar event will be same or later than this given date/time.
        dom - day-of-month that this monthly pickup will recur. May be [1,31] or [-31,-1].
        tod - LocalTime time-of-day when this pickup time recurs
        Returns:
        true if added successfully, false if a duplicate of this event already exists in the calendar.

        Parameters:
        pickupName - of this pickup
        ldtRequest - LocalDateTime the starting date of this pickup. The actual calendar event will be same or later than this given date/time.
